Description: Seed Savers Exchange is a non-profit, 501(c)(3), member supported organization.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: Seed Savers Exchange is a non-profit, 501(c)(3), member supported organization that saves and shares the heirloom seeds of Their garden heritage, forming a living legacy that can be passed down through generations. Their mission is to conserve and promote America's culturally diverse but endangered garden and food crop heritage for future generations by collecting, growing, and sharing heirloom seeds and plants. At the heart of Seed Savers Exchange are the dedicated members who have distributed hundreds of thousands of heirloom and open pollinated garden seeds since Their founding over 37 years ago. Those seeds now are widely used by seed companies, small farmers supplying local and regional markets, chefs and home gardeners and cooks, alike.  Seed Savers Exchange was founded in 1975 by Diane Ott Whealy and Kent Whealy to honor this tradition of preserving and sharing. Their collection started when Diane's terminally-ill grandfather gave them the seeds of two garden plants, Grandpa Ott's morning glory and German Pink tomato. Grandpa Ott's parents brought the seeds from Bavaria when they immigrated to St. Lucas, Iowa in the 1870s.

CircumRent enables soon-to-be moving residents to list and show their apartments to prospective renters. In exchange, CircumRent gives renters a sizeable rebate on their annual rent. Circumrent’s partnership with current residents gives prospective renters the earliest possible access to apartment inventory that no one else knows about, for a fraction of the price of traditional broker services.  No longer will prospective renters be shown around by someone with limited knowledge of the apartment, who are legally bound to withhold certain information. Using Circumrent, prospective renters learn about apartments from residents who are familiar with their apartments, buildings, and neighborhoods and are free to answer all questions. Prospective renters pay less to move in, outgoing residents get paid when they move out, and landlords have zero-downtime units. Everyone wins.

Description: Pharmly is a pharmaceutical marketplace allowing medical facilities to source drugs from pharmaceutical wholesale marketplaces.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Pharmly is a pharmaceutical marketplace that allows medical facilities to source drugs from the $300B pharmaceutical wholesale marketplace when their primary supplier cannot meet their demand due to drug shortages. Everyday, 89% of medical facilities experience a drug shortage and turn to the secondary market. When they do turn to this market, they are often paying in excess of a 400% markup due to limited time & resources to locate product. Pharmly is designed to drive down healthcare costs through its competitive bidding platform.

Its products are ComplianceSeal and Shield Toolkit. ComplianceSeal is an adaptive security information and event monitoring platform with GDPR, healthcare, financial services, and public sector controls built in to enable security, privacy, governance, and compliance.
